      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I have to say I like the ATTUNABLE&amp;nbsp;to ATTUNED best. It also makes one less tag that has to be displayed on a item. If you try to drop a no_drop item which is now called no_trade. You get the message, "&lt;EM&gt;That item cannot be dropped, traded, or sold.&lt;/EM&gt;". &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Currently if you inspect a attunable item that has been used you get, "MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO TRADE ATTUNABLE". You could easily change this to, "MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM ATTUNED". Prior to being euiped it would read, "MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM ATTUNABLE", for example.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO TRADE ATTUNABLE&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM ATTUNABLE&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM ATTUNED&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Some food for thought, prolly a little late for this one, smiles.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
