      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As Luclin being my home server I see new players every week, many that have never played anything like EQ before and in my opinion the change is a very subtle one that will have little or no effect on existing players and have some great effects on new players so why argue about it. It is a small change that can do some real good and will not harm anything and if anything needs changed about it I agree with above that you could just add a message that explains what can be done with the item either in it's inspection window or have the message appear in the chat window when the item is received.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As far as the changes in general to the game go..... Everyone agree's that things need changed and changes no matter how big or subtle are not going to make everyone happy all the time. I submit that instead of everyone threatning to leave the game that you ride it out, make suggestions on what you would like to see changed and input on things that were changed that you think needed to be done different and from there let the overall change to the game happen and see what comes of it in the end. Threatning to leave EQ and flacking the development team is not getting anyone anywhere and if you step back and take a look at where they stand in all of this you have it good because they have people upset with them at every turn and are in a no win situation. Each change made is but a drop in the hat to what the overall picture will be when everything is in place so try inputing what you think should be changed and wait and see what the big picture will be and if you think they ruined the game in the way you like to play then move on. As I see it, it's as simple as that.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Just my 2 coppers worth,&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
